25/04/2004
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- During the North Atlantic Council meeting in Brussels on Friday (23 April), NATO ambassadors praised Macedonia's defence reforms.
Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski was in attendance, together with Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva.
Buckovski said the government had received "compliments" on its implementation of defence reforms, adding that NATO pledged to support their continuation.
He noted that weaknesses were also identified, including problems in the judicial system.
(MIA, Makfax - 23/04/04)
